history.content: See http://summer.berkeley.edu/  and look at the pull-down menus under "Enrollment Changes."  You can also find contact information for summer session if any of that is not as helpful as you would like.

children.subject: go to your dashboard and scroll down to the "student resources" box on the right hand side >> Submit a Form >> Add a Withdrawal Request (i think that's what it is)

history.content:
This may not be the ideal place to ask this, but I was trying to drop a class this summer term (my only one) and I received the following message:

 "You cannot drop this class. Unable to Drop class as it will drop you below the required minimum units for enrollment. If you are attempting to withdraw from the term (drop your last class), you must submit a Withdrawal Request Form on CalCentral."

Does anyone know where the Withdrawal Request Form on CalCentral in located?
history.subject: How to Withdraw from Summer Term?
